Senior citizens in KwaZulu-Natal say they're ready to be vaccinated but are finding it hard to register. eNCA's Lethiwe Mdluli reports. Courtesy #DStv403   JOHANNESBURG - Senior citizens in KwaZulu-Natal say they are ready to be vaccinated but are finding it hard to register. The second phase of the rollout is scheduled to start on Monday for those aged 60 and above. READ: Gauteng pensioners urged to stay at home The provincial Health Department says close to 200,000 people have registered so far. KwaZulu-Natal premier Sihle Zikalala says the province is ready and has established mass vaccination centres where the elderly and frontline workers can get the jab. Watch the video above for more details